1. get a feature request
2. make a branch for it
3. coding your feature
4. commit the code
5. merge master back into the feature branch (because at the time you develop your feature, there could be other things happening in master)
6. push the feature branch onto github/bitbucket
7. ask for a pull request that You want to merge n commits into master branch from feature branch, a code review needed there
8. the guy who review the pull request confirm the merge, and code being merged into the remote master
9. (optionally) you can delete your branch
10. now git pull your master, the change from feature branch has been there in master